<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Habitat and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
This species is known only from the type locality in Chiapas, Mexico. The species inhabits areas with sedimentary soils, mostly formed by sandstones with a thin layer of organic matter, mostly within altered remnants of oak and pine-oak forest. The species with which it coexists are 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Quercus rugosa" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="rugosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Quercus rugosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Née">Nee</normalizedToken>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Inga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Inga vera" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Inga vera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Willd, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trofimov &amp; Rohwer" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Sw." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Damburneya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Damburneya coriacea" order="Laurales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coriacea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Damburneya coriacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Sw.) Trofimov &amp; Rohwer, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Eugenia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eugenia capuli" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capuli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Eugenia capuli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Schltdl. &amp; Cham.) Hook. &amp; Arn., 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Ulmaceae" genus="Trema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trema micrantha" order="Urticales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="micrantha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Trema micrantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Blume, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cecropiaceae" genus="Cecropia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cecropia obtusifolia" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="obtusifolia">
